research/history/memory.json.bak_corrupt_round141:482:      "design_hypothesis": "`routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual` was previously blocked by a training-graph issue: its routers only influenced top-k indices, so DDP could treat router parameters as unused. Routing the selected activation magnitudes themselves should stabilize training and give the architecture a fair mid-K test against the current `K=16` frontier point.",
research/history/memory.json.bak_corrupt_round141:498:        "If it runs cleanly but is clearly worse than the current `K=16` frontier point, retire this routed branch and return to a genuinely new architecture family next round.",
research/history/memory.json.bak_corrupt_round141:499:        "If it still crashes under the fixed launcher, treat the remaining issue as trainer/runtime integration rather than architecture quality and inspect the distributed training path before further family search."
research/history/memory.json.bak_corrupt_round141:535:        "If `lowrank_residual` wins at `K=1`, keep the ultra-low-K lane and then return to a different substantial architecture branch for mid-K exploration.",
research/history/memory.json.bak_corrupt_round141:537:        "If it clearly loses at `K=1`, retain `lowrank_residual` as the best `K=2/4` family and pivot to a different architecture branch rather than minor scalar sweeps."
research/history/memory.json.bak_corrupt_round141:544:      "design_hypothesis": "After eleven non-improving rounds, the next worthwhile move is another fundamentally different architecture rather than any recipe tweak; a plain low-rank gated residual model may outperform the recent codebook, VQ, and adaptive-budget branches at K=24 by using a simpler support-selection mechanism on top of the proven low-rank trunk.",
research/history/memory.json.bak_corrupt_round141:590:      "design_hypothesis": "Five rounds of stagnation mean scalar tweaks are exhausted, so the next move should be a fundamentally different architecture under a controlled recipe rather than more LR or aux changes. `lowrank_grouped_residual` is a materially different low-EF family that enforces group-local competition, and testing it at the frontier-relevant `K=16, EF=12` slot can reveal whether structured support selection improves the mid-K tradeoff over `lowrank_two_stage_residual`.",
research/history/memory.json.bak_corrupt_round141:603:        "If `lowrank_grouped_residual` wins at `K=16`, continue the same architecture-only comparison at `K=24` before changing any scalar hyperparameters.",
research/history/memory.json.bak_corrupt_round141:605:        "If it clearly loses at `K=16`, reject this branch and move to another substantially different built-in architecture rather than returning to minor sweeps."
research/history/memory.json.bak_corrupt_round141:612:      "design_hypothesis": "`lowrank_grouped_residual` clearly lost at `K=16`, so the severe-stagnation policy still points to another fundamentally different architecture rather than more scalar tweaks. `whitened_lowrank_gated_residual` is a materially different low-EF family because it changes the support-selection space through residual preconditioning plus gating, and testing it at the frontier-relevant `K=16, EF=12` slot can reveal whether that combination improves the mid-K transition band over `lowrank_two_stage_residual`.",
research/history/memory.json.bak_corrupt_round141:625:        "If `whitened_lowrank_gated_residual` wins at `K=16`, continue the same architecture-only comparison at `K=24` before changing any scalar hyperparameters.",
research/history/memory.json.bak_corrupt_round141:627:        "If it clearly loses at `K=16`, reject this branch and move to another substantially different built-in architecture rather than minor sweeps."
research/history/memory.json.bak_corrupt_round141:648:        "If it clearly loses at K=24, reject this family quickly and move to another fundamentally different non-lowrank architecture rather than returning to scalar sweeps.",
research/history/memory.json.bak_corrupt_round141:670:        "If `jumprelu` clearly loses at K=24, reject this family quickly and move to another non-lowrank architecture such as `two_stage_residual` rather than any scalar sweep.",
research/history/memory.json.bak_corrupt_round141:744:      "design_hypothesis": "After repeated failures from gating, staged residual, batch-budget, and codebook families, the next fundamentally different mechanism is a low-rank feature-mixing encoder without residual trunks: `factorized_topk` at `K=24, EF=12` may improve latent scoring efficiency enough to recover a better mid-K FVU tradeoff than the recent non-frontier architectures.",
research/history/memory.json.bak_corrupt_round141:810:      "design_hypothesis": "After `residual_vq` and `codebook_topk` both underperformed at `K=24`, a deeper discrete coarse stage is the next fundamentally different architecture worth testing: `two_code_residual_vq` may recover more shared structure before sparse correction and produce a better mid-K FVU/K tradeoff than the single-code discrete families.",
research/history/memory.json.bak_corrupt_round141:832:      "design_hypothesis": "After thirteen non-improving rounds, the next useful step is another fundamentally different architecture rather than any recipe tweak; `bucketed_lowrank_residual` may recover a better K=24 tradeoff by routing samples between specialized low-rank residual dictionaries instead of forcing one global selector.",
research/history/memory.json.bak_corrupt_round141:943:        "If `topk` wins at K=24, follow with K=16 or K=32 to map whether the simpler architecture generalizes across the mid-K band."
research/history/memory.json.bak_corrupt_round141:1048:      "design_hypothesis": "After fourteen non-improving rounds, the next useful move is still a fundamentally different architecture rather than any recipe tweak; `lowrank_multi_branch_residual` may recover a better K=24 tradeoff by letting multiple low-rank residual branches specialize instead of forcing one shared residual pathway.",
research/history/memory.json.bak_corrupt_round141:1178:      "design_hypothesis": "After five rounds of stagnation on the bucketed backbone, minor recipe tweaks are no longer the highest-value action. A fundamentally different but still closely related architecture, `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`, may perform better in the operator-mandated `EF=16` regime at `K=32` by avoiding the bucketing path that now appears saturated while preserving the strong two-stage soft-codebook structure.",
research/history/memory.json.bak_corrupt_round141:1352:      "design_hypothesis": "After bucketed, plain two-stage, routed, and gated soft-codebook backbones all failed to beat the current `K=32, EF=16` bucketed point, the next severe-stagnation move should test a genuinely different existing architecture rather than return to scalar tweaks. `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` is the strongest remaining soft-codebook-adjacent candidate by prior quality and may transfer better to `EF=16` at `K=32` by allocating capacity asymmetrically across stages instead of via buckets, routing, or gating.",
research/history/memory.json.bak_corrupt_round141:1375:        "If it clearly loses at `K=32`, treat the remaining soft-codebook architecture space as close to exhausted under the current recipe and pivot to under-explored runtime axes on the existing bucketed backbone."
research/history/memory.json.bak_corrupt_round141:1382:      "design_hypothesis": "After three distinct K32 soft-codebook backbones failed to beat the bucketed point under `EF=16`, the next severe-stagnation step should continue architecture search only along an already-registered but mechanistically different branch rather than return to scalar tweaks. `lowrank_gated_soft_codebook_residual` is the strongest remaining soft-codebook variant by prior results and may yield a better small-K tradeoff at `K=32, EF=16` by using learned gating instead of bucket partitioning or hard routing.",
