research/history/round_summaries/round_0228.json:37:      "\u5f53\u524d `0.13x~0.21x` \u7684 matched architecture probes \u4e5f\u5df2\u8fde\u7eed\u7ed9\u51fa\u8d1f\u4fe1\u53f7\uff1a`factorized_expert_topk`\u3001`factorized_topk`\u3001`lowrank_expert_topk`\u3001`shared_two_stage_residual_expert`\u3001`shared_routed_expert_topk` \u90fd\u672a\u628a objective \u62c9\u56de r212 \u9644\u8fd1\u3002",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0184.json:19:    "hypothesis": "候选 family 设为 `factorized_expert_topk`。最终重构公式为 `x_hat = Σ_{e∈E(h(x))} Σ_{i∈S_e(h(x))} α_{e,i}(h(x)) b_{e,i}`，其中 `h(x)=ReLU(Bx)` 是共享低维投影，`E(h(x))` 是轻量 router 选出的少量 active experts，`{b_{e,i}}` 是各 expert 的静态子库原子；在线侧可直接导出为“shared low-rank projection + 轻量 expert 路由 + expert 子库查表 + 有限加权求和”的 LUTurbo/Lottable 推理链路，静态库不随样本动态生成，因此兼容性判断为 `扩展兼容`。`batch_topk`、`adaptive_budget_topk` 这类 batch/sample-coupled family 仍是 `不兼容`，只能作历史参考，不能驱动当前 frontier。r183 的新 family `shared_two_stage_residual_expert` 在约 `0.24x` 下仅做到 `FVU=0.1411`，说明“shared coarse trunk + routed residual cleanup”这条 two-stage 变体没有打败现有 low-cost anchor；因此下一步更高信息量的问题不是继续在 shared/coarse 线上补参数，而是转向当前高优先级但尚未在这条 exact low-cost recipe 上 fresh 验证的“expert 内部 low-rank / small head”槽位。相对 r176 只把 `ARCHITECTURE` 从 `expert_topk` 切到 `factorized_expert_topk`，保持 `K=108`、`EXPANSION_FACTOR=1`、`NUM_EXPERTS=64`、`ACTIVE_EXPERTS=2`、`LATENTS_PER_EXPERT=160`、`FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM=256`、`adam`、`LR=8e-4` 与其余训练配方不变，直接回答“把 routed-only expert 的 full-dim 局部 scorer 换成 shared bottleneck + expert-specific small head，能否在更低总成本下修复 r176 的质量缺口”。，基于当前成本口径复核，该配置仍位于预期成本带内并满足预算约束。",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0184.json:38:      "r183 的 `shared_two_stage_residual_expert` 已在约 `0.24x` 失败并归档，当前不应继续沿 shared-coarse two-stage 线做局部参数补点。"
research/history/round_summaries/round_0070.json:19:    "hypothesis": "Final reconstruction stays x_hat = sum_{r=1..R} beta_r(x) u_r + sum_{i in S_{e(x-t(x))}(x-t(x))} alpha_{e,i}(x) b_{e,i}, with t(x) = sum_{r=1..R} beta_r(x) u_r. This exports to the LUTurbo/Lottable path as a static trunk table lookup plus a single routed static expert sublibrary lookup plus a finite weighted sum, so `lowrank_expert_topk` is extended-compatible. Compatibility screen before proposing this round: `expert_topk` is directly compatible; `lowrank_expert_topk`, `lowrank_expert_residual`, and `two_stage_residual_expert` are extended-compatible; batch-coupled families such as `batch_topk` and `adaptive_budget_topk` are incompatible and must stay off the active frontier. Relative to r60, changing only `TRUNK_RANK` from 64 to 32 tests the missing mid-trunk point in the low-cost band: if the routed-only improvement from r59 to r60 was not all-or-nothing, this should recover much of r60's FVU while moving left from the current lowrank+expert anchor and potentially create a new compatible Pareto segment between `expert_topk` and `lowrank_expert_residual`.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0070.json:20:    "summary": "Use Round 70 for a low-cost structural probe in `lowrank_expert_topk`: start from r60 and only reduce `TRUNK_RANK` to 32. The goal is to map whether shared low-rank trunk width can produce a new compatible Pareto point in the 0.3x-0.5x band, instead of continuing plain-selector K sweeps or more local cleanup on `lowrank_expert_residual`.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0070.json:25:    "self_review": "This satisfies the single-variable param-only rule and stays within an already implemented compatible family. It directly answers a higher-value structural question than another `expert_topk` K move, and it avoids spending Round 70 on further local polishing of the current `lowrank_expert_residual` mainline after r66 already showed diminishing returns from more trunk compression there.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0070.json:40:      "If `TRUNK_RANK=32` keeps most of r60 quality at materially lower total_cost, next do a matched `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_expert_residual` switch from this point to measure whether residual cleanup is still worth paying for at the same trunk width.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0070.json:41:      "If `TRUNK_RANK=32` falls back close to the routed-only `expert_topk` band, treat that as evidence that `lowrank_expert_topk` has a sharp trunk-width floor and shift low-cost budget back to `lowrank_expert_residual` or pure `expert_topk` rather than more MoE-capacity expansion.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0070.json:62:    "description": "Use Round 70 for a low-cost structural probe in `lowrank_expert_topk`: start from r60 and only reduce `TRUNK_RANK` to 32. The goal is to map whether shared low-rank trunk width can produce a new compatible Pareto point in the 0.3x-0.5x band, instead of continuing plain-selector K sweeps or more local cleanup on `lowrank_expert_residual`.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0070.json:63:    "self_review": "This satisfies the single-variable param-only rule and stays within an already implemented compatible family. It directly answers a higher-value structural question than another `expert_topk` K move, and it avoids spending Round 70 on further local polishing of the current `lowrank_expert_residual` mainline after r66 already showed diminishing returns from more trunk compression there.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0218.json:7:  "family_name": "shared_lowrank_two_stage_residual_expert",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0218.json:19:    "hypothesis": "\u5019\u9009 family \u8bbe\u4e3a `shared_lowrank_two_stage_residual_expert`\u3002\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u516c\u5f0f\u5199\u4e3a `x_hat = \u03a3_{i\u2208S_shared(h(x))} \u03b1_i^sh(x) u_i + \u03a3_{e\u2208E(r_1(x))} \u03a3_{j\u2208S_e(r_1(x))} \u03b3_{e,j}(x) b_{e,j}`\uff0c\u5176\u4e2d `h(x)` \u662f shared low-rank bottleneck\uff0c`r_1(x)=x-\u03a3_{i\u2208S_shared(h(x))} \u03b1_i^sh(x) u_i` \u662f coarse stage \u540e\u7684\u6b8b\u5dee\uff0c`{u_i}` \u662f\u9759\u6001 shared/coarse \u5411\u91cf\u5e93\uff0c`{b_{e,j}}` \u662f\u9759\u6001 routed residual expert \u5b50\u5e93\u3002\u5728\u7ebf\u4fa7\u53ef\u76f4\u63a5\u5bfc\u51fa\u5230 LUTurbo/Lottable \u7684\u201cshared low-rank \u7c97\u67e5\u8868 + residual expert \u5b50\u5e93\u9009\u62e9/\u67e5\u8868 + \u6709\u9650\u52a0\u6743\u6c42\u548c + \u9009\u62e9\u6027\u8865\u507f\u201d\u63a8\u7406\u94fe\u8def\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u8be5 family \u5224\u5b9a\u4e3a `\u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9`\u3002`expert_topk`\u3001`shared_routed_expert_topk` \u7b49\u4ecd\u662f\u517c\u5bb9 family\uff1b`batch_topk`\u3001`adaptive_budget_topk` \u7b49 batch/sample-coupled family \u4ecd\u5c5e `\u4e0d\u517c\u5bb9`\uff0c\u4e0d\u80fd\u9a71\u52a8\u5f53\u524d objective leaderboard\u3002\u672c\u8f6e\u552f\u4e00\u4e3b\u5047\u8bbe\u662f\uff1a\u5728 r217 \u5df2\u7ecf\u57fa\u672c\u8bc1\u4f2a\u201c\u66f4\u8f7b factorized shared+routed scorer\u201d\u4e4b\u540e\uff0c\u5f53\u524d\u6700\u6709\u4fe1\u606f\u589e\u91cf\u7684\u672a\u9a8c\u8bc1\u7ed3\u6784\u69fd\u4f4d\u4e0d\u518d\u662f\u7ee7\u7eed\u505a shared+routed \u7684\u8f7b\u5fae\u53d8\u4f53\uff0c\u800c\u662f\u76f4\u63a5\u6d4b\u8bd5\u66f4\u4e0d\u5bf9\u79f0\u7684\u201cshared low-rank coarse branch \u5403\u4e3b\u5e72\uff0crouted experts \u53ea\u505a residual cleanup\u201d\u3002\u56e0\u6b64\u76f8\u5bf9 r212 \u4ec5\u628a `ARCHITECTURE` \u4ece `expert_topk` \u5207\u5230 `shared_lowrank_two_stage_residual_expert`\uff0c\u4fdd\u6301 `K=32`\u3001`EXPANSION_FACTOR=1`\u3001`OPTIMIZER=adam`\u3001`LR=8e-4` \u4ee5\u53ca\u5176\u4f59\u4e3b recipe \u4e0d\u53d8\uff0c\u76f4\u63a5\u56de\u7b54\u8fd9\u4e2a\u7ed3\u6784\u69fd\u4f4d\u672c\u8eab\u503c\u4e0d\u503c\u5f97\u7ee7\u7eed\u3002\u672c\u5730\u590d\u6838\u663e\u793a\u8be5\u70b9 selection_accesses=737280\u3001deployment_accesses=163840\u3001combined_accesses=901120\uff0c\u5bf9\u5f53\u524d 1024x4096 fused-QKV proxy \u7684 exact total_cost_ratio=0.21484375\uff1b\u76f8\u5bf9 r212 \u7684 exact 0.1640625 \u589e\u52a0\u4e86 0.05078125\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u82e5\u8981\u5237\u65b0\u5f53\u524d anchor\uff0c\u9700\u8981 exceed \u538b\u5230\u7ea6 `\u22640.1406937575`\u3002\u8fd9\u4e2a\u95e8\u69db\u5f88\u9ad8\uff0c\u4f46\u4e5f\u6b63\u662f\u672c\u8f6e probe \u7684\u4ef7\u503c\u6240\u5728\uff1a\u5982\u679c\u8fde\u6700\u8d34\u8fd1\u201cshared low-rank trunk + residual experts\u201d\u4f18\u5148\u65b9\u5411\u7684 matched probe \u90fd\u4e0d\u80fd\u663e\u8457\u7f29\u5c0f exceed \u7f3a\u53e3\uff0c\u5c31\u53ef\u4ee5\u66f4\u679c\u65ad\u5730\u4e0b\u8c03\u8fd9\u6761\u7ed3\u6784\u7ebf\u5728\u5f53\u524d hookpoint \u7684\u4f18\u5148\u7ea7\u3002",
